storyInfo: A survivor walks alone on the path of revenge. To find the traitors hiding in the shadows, she requires strength even more formidable.

attributes.content: They told me it was all over.
My homeland, my companions, everything buried now.
But I knew, it had only just begun.
...And I'm on my way.
04:50 P.M. \ Overcast
A town in northern Kazimierz
Here you go. Bread and clean water, all in here.
attributes.name: Kazimierz Villager

attributes.content: Incredible, you are! Fought 'em off, no, wiped 'em out alone, all those gloompincers... Didn't expect one young lady like you'd finish up that job in half an afternoon.
attributes.name: Kazimierz Villager

attributes.content: Even going out all together, the young'uns couldn't handle it.
attributes.name: Kazimierz Villager

attributes.content: Frankly, it gave me a scare, our town being so small. And I've never seen someone fight as ferocious as you.
attributes.name: Kazimierz Villager

attributes.content: ...I'll be fine without.
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: Don't want any bread or water? Well... alright, we've got some medicine here too.
attributes.name: Kazimierz Villager

attributes.content: It's from the caravan that passed through last time. We had to trade them a good amount for it. They were worth plenty, I'll tell you.
attributes.name: Kazimierz Villager

attributes.content: By the sights of it, you've been hurt bad, haven't you? You could probably use it.
attributes.name: Kazimierz Villager

attributes.content: I don't need it.
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: Th-Then what do you need? Gold coins? That'll be tough. We're only a little town, and rabble comes by shaking us down every few days, plus all the beasts making trouble out there...
attributes.name: Kazimierz Villager

attributes.content: Our pockets are all emptied out by the end of the year. Barely a penny we've got.
attributes.name: Kazimierz Villager

attributes.content: The day before. People sighted a Kuranta the day before, black clothing and a crossbow, heading this way.
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: Tell me where they are.
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: Crossbow? The kind you use for hunting?
attributes.name: Kazimierz Villager

attributes.content: The kind to murder.
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: M-Murder?
attributes.name: Kazimierz Villager

attributes.content: You've got to be joking... no, the look in your eyes says you aren't joking one bit... how frightful... *cough* How could someone like that show up in a little place like ours?
attributes.name: Kazimierz Villager

attributes.content: Don't screw with me.
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: I-I-I-I-Is that a weapon? Don't, erm, please don't shoot! I swear, I haven't seen anyone like the person you describe—
attributes.name: Kazimierz Villager

attributes.content: The ones in the last village saw. And told me. They went this way.
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: Per... perhaps they already passed through here, went south? There's an even bigger town that way, more food, cleaner water...
attributes.name: Kazimierz Villager

attributes.content: Oh, god, Heaven above! Miss, god, believe me, please, I've got no reason to lie to you at all.
attributes.name: Kazimierz Villager

attributes.content: Look, please, here, this is the last of my family's money, we were saving it for the year-end tax, this is all we've got, have it, have it all...
attributes.name: Kazimierz Villager

attributes.content: I said, I don't need it.
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: Forget it. You can go.
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: Another day, empty-handed.
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: But no matter. You can't hide much longer.
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: I'll be following you. All the way—until I find you, one, by one, all of you.
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: What's this?
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: Bread, and water. And medicine.
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: He was scared so bad, he ran off without a trace, and yet he still deliberately came back in after.
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: Is he trying to show thanks? But it was only a few gloompincers, nothing more. It took no effort on my part.
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: People like him... do remind me... of back then.
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: Grandpa, who are they? Are they the nice knights everyone talks about?
They aren't...?
Are the things they're carrying like the ones the bad people use to pick on us?
I... I'm sort of scared.
But they're good people, right? They helped us fight off the bad people.
I want to say thank you to them.
I don't really have any good stuff to give them. Would this half of my scone be okay? I can play a harmonica song for them too.
Mm-hm, I hope they can stay with.
With all of us, forever.
Now all that's left is this harmonica.
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: Nice knights? *sigh*...
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: Whether then, or now... it's all the same.
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: If they're still around... if...
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: It's too bad—there is no 'if.'
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: Hey, someone's here!
attributes.name: Kazimierz Ruffian

attributes.content: Whoa, and a bunch of food—not much good, but good enough to eat tonight.
attributes.name: Kazimierz Ruffian

attributes.content: Leave.
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: Did you just tell me to leave? Who do you think you are?
attributes.name: Kazimierz Ruffian

attributes.content: It's just sitting here. Is there a name on it? I don't see you eating it. I found it now, so it's mine.
attributes.name: Kazimierz Ruffian

attributes.content: Then just take it and get lost.
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: Wait up, what's that you're holding? A harmonica? Heh, some tacky toy. Whatever. Take it to the city, you might find some boring old guy who thinks it's worth something.
attributes.name: Kazimierz Ruffian

attributes.content: This is not for you to touch.
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: Oh, you talk pretty tough, don't you?
attributes.name: Kazimierz Ruffian

attributes.content: Who do you even think I am, brat?
attributes.name: Kazimierz Ruffian

attributes.content: Just look at you. How long has it been since you ate something?
attributes.name: Kazimierz Ruffian

attributes.content: I'm warning you—*cough*, *cough* *cough*.
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: Jeez. You seem pretty sick at that. You'd best believe I could knock you over with a single poke.
attributes.name: Kazimierz Ruffian

attributes.content: What'cha playing at? Don't spook me now, it's dark out here. You think you can threaten anyone with a bare tree branch?
attributes.name: Kazimierz Ruffian

attributes.content: I gave you plenty of warning. You didn't listen.
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: Ow, ff-ow-ow-ow—that's a crossbow! That's the kind that kills people, isn't it?!
attributes.name: Kazimierz Ruffian

attributes.content: Get. Lost.
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: I don't want to kill anyone tonight. At the very least, not you.
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: Spare me... bud, just spare me! You can have this, have it all back.
attributes.name: Kazimierz Ruffian

attributes.content: I'm outta here, I promise!
attributes.name: Kazimierz Ruffian

attributes.content: Mm... *cough* *cough*, *cough* *cough* *cough*.
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: Who's there?
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: *cough* *cough* *cough* *cough*...
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: I have to stay up... stay awake.
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: I still haven't... I...
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: I still haven't found those traitors yet.
So long as that day doesn't come, they can never rest in peace—
And I can never, ever stop.
Hello? Are you okay?
Seems she hasn't passed out completely... though she's at the point she can't stand.
Identity confirmation... yes, just like in the mission description. This should be the target, no mistake.
Serious wounds, fever temperatures, and gravely malnourished... she hasn't eaten properly in forever, and hasn't slept, either.
Nutritional supplements... and some emergency meds... Lucky I packed enough for the road. Dr. Kal'tsit really sees every last thing coming.
You're up.
Who are you?!
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: Don't be alarmed, I mean you no harm. I'm employed by a pharmaceutical company named Rhodes Island. I'm responsible for field work in this area. Here, this is my work ID.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: That doesn't prove anything. IDs and papers and whatever can all be forged.
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: Fair enough, they can. Haha, you're just like I heard. An extremely cautious youngster.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Heard? From who?
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: Oh, jeez, don't get all tense again.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Look, I'm serious, I'm not anyone bad. I don't even have any weapons that big or lethal on me. At best, I've got a couple of tools for defending myself from beasts.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: I've got nothing on you. I see that crossbow of yours... look, it's still right there. You could reach out and grab it.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Can we have a real talk now?
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: If you're up to something, you'll regret having stepped into this forest.
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: Yes. I believe you. The crossbow in your hands has already told me that much.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Right now, you need to tell me. Who was it that told you anything about me?
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: That's... er...
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: There's been reports of a very young Elafia girl who's been all around the northern villages of Kazimierz lately, looking for any leads on a specific group. Plenty of people have been picking up on it, actually.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: The footprints left behind when tracking prey.
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: I wouldn't have made a mistake like that in the past... but I don't care that I have.
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: Who told you to look for me?
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: That'd be Rhodes Island. Just like I introduced earlier, Rhodes Island is a pharmaceutical company, doing business in all areas. They've been seeking all sorts of suitable talent, too, and they'd like to invite you to join.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: A pharmaceutical company?
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: Did you drug me just now?
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: Only some nutritional supplements and a simple first-aid medication. I'm no Medic Operator. I personally can't give you any better of an examination, nor further treatment.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: You look a good bit better now, luckily. Your injuries should be holding decently. If we want any further diagnosis, you'll need to come back to Rhodes Island with me.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: To treat me. And you want to hire me.
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: Seeing as you've investigated, you should already know. I don't understand the first thing about medicine. The only thing I can do is fight.
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: So, what would a pharmaceutical company want a hired bow for?
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: Er... oh, boy, that one... er, like I said earlier, Rhodes Island does a lot of business, and frequently comes into contact with a lot of different people in a lot of different areas.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: And during those contacts, we unavoidably run into some emergencies.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: At times like that, we need people with special skills like yours, to help give Rhodes Island a fighting chance.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Whether person or organization, you have to have strength if you want to survive.
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: Right. I'm sure you can understand.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: But my strength has other uses.
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: Do you mean those people you're looking for?
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Yes.
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: Every day I haven't found them is one more day my footsteps will not cease.
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: I understand... I'm not too clear about your past, but it's a very common thing, isn't it? Just like us inside Rhodes Island. We've got scores of operators, all with their own differing and individual attachments.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Is that so?
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: We won't ever interfere in an operator's private affairs, and outside of missions, everyone has freedom.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Beyond that, when an operator needs it, providing aid doesn't go against our standards, Rhodes Island will provide whatever you want—medical service, crucial information, or necessary strength.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: It's why a good few Operators chose to join Rhodes Island, really.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Then the people I need to find...
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: Can Rhodes Island help me there?
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: It's not my place to say anything else. Just, us helping you look for someone—that'd be more effective than you going it alone around Kazimierz, or even areas beyond, right?
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Alone, you probably wouldn't hold out for too long. You're short on supplies, and you don't have any help.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: I'll be honest, you're not in the best of shape right now. If you need to find someone, accomplish some goal, then first you need to ensure your survival, right?
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: How do I put it? In our world, if you want to get something done, even if it's as bare and simple as staying alive, a bunch of heads all together always beats one.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: (Days with no help, only able to rely on myself to live... It's not like I've never gone through times like these.)
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: (The feeling of someone there to help... I can't deny... day in, day out, I miss it.)
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: (In that case, this should go a little quicker now.)
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: You're right.
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: Rhodes Island... a pharmaceutical company. Not out to do anything bad, right?
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: On that point, you can rest assured.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Alright. So long as you're willing to lend me more strength—
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: I can lend my strength to you.
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: I'll join.
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: That's wonderful, then! I won't ask for much more information. Once we get back to Rhodes Island, there'll be HR operators who'll check with you separately.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: After all the red tape's done with, you can officially become a Rhodes Island Operator.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: I think I can say it'll be a delight to work together with, er...? Um, what should I call you?
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: ...Firewatch.
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: Past, present, future... no matter where I am.
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: Until I find every last traitor, until I fulfill my revenge—
attributes.name: Firewatch

attributes.content: This will be the only name I possess.
attributes.name: Firewatch
